WEBVTT

00:12.930 --> 00:15.342
Would you leave her alone?

00:15.516 --> 00:18.303
It's your own fault.
You and your insane affection...

00:18.477 --> 00:20.559
-...for stupid cattle.
-Just go away.

00:20.730 --> 00:23.517
I wouldn't have to be here
if the Magister could trust you.

00:23.691 --> 00:29.607
l fulfilled the conditions of my sentence.
I murdered this innocent girl.

00:29.780 --> 00:32.863
There was no murder.
You drained her blood and gave her yours.

00:33.034 --> 00:34.490
l've proven my loyalty.

00:34.660 --> 00:37.618
Yes. But you're romantic,
you're sentimental.

00:37.788 --> 00:42.248
You just might do something to keep
the little bloodbag from joining our ranks.

00:42.418 --> 00:47.082
I'll follow my orders. I won't let you
stake her before she goes to ground.

00:49.634 --> 00:53.297
I'm not gonna stake her,
I'm gonna set her free.

00:53.471 --> 00:58.056
You've already set her free.
The same as Eric freed me.

00:58.226 --> 01:01.309
Everyone she's ever known
will recoil from her.

01:01.479 --> 01:04.061
Everything she's ever loved
has been stolen from her.

01:04.232 --> 01:06.348
Oh, please, there's no comparison.

01:06.525 --> 01:09.232
You've given that
pathetic lump of temporary flesh...

01:09.403 --> 01:12.645
-Jessica.
-...the ultimate gift.

01:12.823 --> 01:16.941
-You're a maker. You're a hero.
-I find myself doubting...

01:17.119 --> 01:21.237
-...whether you were ever truly human.
-Thank you.

01:23.459 --> 01:24.869
Damn you.

01:25.044 --> 01:28.502
Once she's planted in the earth,
the transformation will begin.

01:28.839 --> 01:32.423
-I know.
-|'|| tuck you in.

01:33.010 --> 01:34.921
Tomorrow night...

01:36.347 --> 01:40.465
...your little girl will rise a vampire.

03:18.532 --> 03:18.861
This is Tara.
Leave a message. Easy stuff.

03:18.866 --> 03:22.199
This is Tara.
Leave a message. Easy stuff.

03:22.370 --> 03:24.907
Hey, Tara, where you at?
At least let me know...

03:25.081 --> 03:27.914
...you're not drunk in a ditch somewhere.

03:28.542 --> 03:31.033
I'm sorry, I take it back. Just call, okay?

03:33.255 --> 03:34.870
Hey.

03:35.299 --> 03:38.632
I had to put those clothes in the wash.

03:38.803 --> 03:41.966
It felt like the killer was all over me.

03:42.139 --> 03:43.675
Watching me, hating me...

03:43.849 --> 03:49.469
...itching for a knife
or a rope or my neck.

03:49.647 --> 03:55.017
-You didn't get any sense of who it was?
-No, just pictures.

03:55.194 --> 04:00.530
His thoughts were
all red and black and snarly.

04:01.158 --> 04:02.819
But there was something familiar.

04:02.993 --> 04:07.407
Like somebody from Bon Temps?
Or somebody from the bar?

04:07.581 --> 04:10.323
No one I could recognize for sure.

04:11.627 --> 04:14.869
-Look, I think we should call the police.
-And what would I say?

04:15.047 --> 04:17.584
"Sheriff Dearborne, Andy Bellefleur,
I saw a woman die.

04:17.758 --> 04:20.545
| just happened to be
in somebody else's brain at the time"?

04:20.719 --> 04:23.756
Did you get a good look at her?
I mean, what was she like?

04:23.931 --> 04:27.173
Young, pretty...

04:27.435 --> 04:28.470
...with an apron.

04:28.644 --> 04:32.478
-Apron. You mean like a mom?
-More like a waitress.

04:33.983 --> 04:37.521
Was there a nametag?

04:37.862 --> 04:40.194
-Maybe.
-Yeah.

04:41.490 --> 04:43.446
What did it say?

04:45.870 --> 04:47.610
I don't know.

04:50.166 --> 04:53.158
l was looking at her eyes.

04:53.335 --> 04:55.997
She was so surprised.

04:59.800 --> 05:03.509
Well, do you wanna call Bill?
I mean, that might make you feel better.

05:04.180 --> 05:07.843
No. He would've felt how scared I was.

05:08.017 --> 05:10.804
He would've known I was in danger.

05:10.978 --> 05:14.015
If he didn't show up tonight...

05:14.190 --> 05:18.058
-...he's not coming back.
-Hey.

05:24.241 --> 05:27.904
-You hear from Tara?
-No.

05:35.544 --> 05:39.537
Well, good night.

05:41.550 --> 05:43.165
Night.

06:05.616 --> 06:08.858
-Copy that.
-A woman. At 2 in the morning.

06:09.036 --> 06:11.118
Standing there naked,
fucking with my head.

06:11.288 --> 06:13.449
-And she was with a pig?
-A big pig.

06:13.624 --> 06:17.116
Like, you know, like a crazy-ass
motherfucking Paul Bunyan pig.

06:17.294 --> 06:19.785
-Tara, tell the truth.
-That is the truth.

06:19.964 --> 06:21.454
Kenya, I'm an excellent driver...

06:21.632 --> 06:25.250
...but you can't prepare for a naked lady
and a hog in the middle of the road.

06:25.427 --> 06:28.464
-Now, you know that.
-I know you drunk, that's what I know.

06:28.973 --> 06:31.965
Drunk? I'm not drunk. One beer.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.676
Coming from Arlene's party
with an open bottle.

06:34.853 --> 06:37.105
-What bottle?
-The one busted in your car.

06:37.273 --> 06:38.353
That's not my bottle.

06:38.691 --> 06:41.933
-Then you wouldn't mind a sobriety test.
-Hell, no. Bring it.

06:42.653 --> 06:43.984
Step away from the vehicle.

06:44.780 --> 06:47.988
Stand with your feet together.
Stand with one foot in front...

06:48.158 --> 06:52.948
...holding the other one 6 inches
off the ground, parallel to the ground.

06:53.747 --> 06:56.159
-Let's try that again.
-What is the matter with you?

06:56.333 --> 06:58.745
-You know, you turning into Lettie Mae.
-Fuck you.

06:59.295 --> 07:02.913
I am a sheriff's deputy now.
Tara Thornton, don't you go there with me.

07:04.425 --> 07:09.135
Kenya, sister,
the only place I wanna go is home.

07:10.097 --> 07:13.260
Well, sorry, not tonight.

07:13.434 --> 07:18.519
-No. It's not fair. It's not my fault.
-I will cuff you.

07:18.689 --> 07:21.852
-But the lady and the pig, that was real.
-Yeah.

07:22.026 --> 07:25.018
Just watch your intoxicated head,
please.

07:25.821 --> 07:30.406
Jesus fucking Christ. Shit. Fuck.
Amy, what did you do?

07:30.576 --> 07:33.033
I did what we had to do.
Now, come on, wipe up.

07:33.203 --> 07:36.036
Here's a towel.
There's more rags. Come on.

07:37.833 --> 07:39.073
Who the fuck are you?

07:42.338 --> 07:45.045
How can you say that to me?
You know who I am.

07:45.215 --> 07:47.877
-You know better than anybody.
-I thought I knew.

07:48.052 --> 07:51.010
-I told you to let him go.
-Well, I told you not to talk to him.

07:51.180 --> 07:53.216
-He was controlling your mind.
-Bullshit.

07:53.390 --> 07:54.596
-Yes.
-No, not Eddie.

07:54.767 --> 07:59.056
He didn't know how to do that yet.
He trusted me. It was gonna be all right.

07:59.229 --> 08:02.562
God, it was never gonna be all right.
From the minute we took him...

08:02.733 --> 08:05.395
...you knew it'd end like this.
You just couldn't face it.

08:05.569 --> 08:10.154
-I didn't think it would fucking end like this.
-You wanted his blood, bad.

08:10.324 --> 08:12.440
You were with me the whole way,
so don't act...

08:12.618 --> 08:16.031
...like this is all my fault.
Now, I said to clean up, so clean up.

08:16.205 --> 08:19.743
-Yankee bitch.
-Dumb fucking hillbilly.

08:29.426 --> 08:30.757
God.

08:46.151 --> 08:50.394
Listen. It's okay. It's gonna be all right.
We just gotta keep our shit together.

08:54.576 --> 08:57.909
-We killed a man.
-No.

08:58.080 --> 09:02.494
-Yeah.
-For the last time, he was already dead.

09:02.668 --> 09:03.874
He was not a man.

09:04.044 --> 09:07.707
He was a predator, only we got him first.

09:08.716 --> 09:12.629
So don't do this, okay?
Don't let a vampire come between us.

09:13.971 --> 09:15.632
No. I guess not.

09:16.140 --> 09:20.509
Because what we have, Jason...

09:22.146 --> 09:23.977
...it's beautiful.

09:26.567 --> 09:28.228
Yeah.

09:31.613 --> 09:33.149
Yeah.

09:41.832 --> 09:45.950
Good morning.
I didn't know you were up.

09:46.128 --> 09:49.336
-Eggs and sausage, warm in the oven.
-Oh, thanks.

09:51.508 --> 09:54.420
