45:35.817 --> 45:37.557
It's the company.

45:37.736 --> 45:39.442
Must be.

45:40.322 --> 45:42.654
I mean, that says something for us.

45:42.824 --> 45:46.442
We can enjoy ourselves even when
we're trying to find a murderer.

45:47.329 --> 45:51.538
You are fun. It's one of the reasons
I'm still working for you.

45:51.708 --> 45:54.996
-Yeah?
-|t's not the tips or the high-class clientele.

45:56.963 --> 45:58.499
You know what?

45:59.841 --> 46:02.833
It was probably the best day of my life...

46:03.303 --> 46:05.885
...when you walked in looking for a job.

46:06.056 --> 46:08.593
-Quit.
-No, I mean it.

46:13.355 --> 46:15.095
I know you do.

46:17.192 --> 46:19.399
Are you looking in my head?

46:20.779 --> 46:22.690
I'm looking in your heart.

46:40.548 --> 46:41.833
Stop!

46:47.055 --> 46:48.591
No! Bill!

46:52.143 --> 46:55.226
Stop fighting, you stupid men!

46:56.064 --> 46:58.680
-He had his hands all over you.
-She's not your property.

46:58.858 --> 47:02.396
Sam, I can speak for myself. You left me
alone with no promise to come back.

47:02.570 --> 47:05.528
Then you attack the man helping
keep me safe. How dare you?

47:05.699 --> 47:08.566
-He's helping because I asked him to.
-Get out!

47:12.247 --> 47:14.909
If you knew what I had done
to return to you....

47:15.375 --> 47:17.957
I rescind your invitation.

47:19.587 --> 47:21.202
Sookie, don't.

47:21.589 --> 47:23.090
Please.

47:25.343 --> 47:26.924
SooMe.

47:29.597 --> 47:31.212
Please.

47:42.777 --> 47:45.189
Can't you see what he's really like?

47:45.363 --> 47:48.446
-How can you think about being with him?
-My living room's wrecked.

47:48.616 --> 47:51.403
I've got a killer, a vampire
and a shape-shifter on my plate.

47:51.578 --> 47:54.945
Right about now, I'm not thinking about
being with anybody.

48:04.507 --> 48:06.463
This is where you live?

48:07.385 --> 48:08.716
Fuck me.

48:09.596 --> 48:11.962
Come on in, Tara.
Make yourself at home.

48:12.307 --> 48:13.422
If you insist.

48:13.975 --> 48:15.806
I insist. Come on.

48:39.375 --> 48:40.911
I knew it was you.

48:41.086 --> 48:43.077
I knew it from the second
we found Maudette.

48:43.630 --> 48:46.337
People said, "No, not Jason Stackhouse,
he's too dumb."

48:46.508 --> 48:51.298
But I knew. I said, "That shifty
bastard's a goddamn psychopath."

48:51.471 --> 48:54.338
-I ain't arguing with you, Andy.
-Detective.

48:55.016 --> 48:57.598
-Tell us all about it, son.
-|'|| tell you all about it.

48:57.769 --> 49:01.682
I'll tell you exactly what happened.
This piece of shit lured those poor girls...

49:01.856 --> 49:05.189
...into his king-sized bed and dirty sheets
to fuck them and kill them.

49:05.360 --> 49:08.352
Andy, he called us. Let the boy confess.

49:08.530 --> 49:10.612
Go ahead, Jason. How'd it happen?

49:13.451 --> 49:16.568
-I don't know.
-Oh, don't even try that on.

49:16.746 --> 49:19.863
Bud, give me five minutes alone with him.
I'll get you every detail.

49:20.041 --> 49:23.374
-What do you mean, you don't know?
-I don't remember what I done.

49:25.338 --> 49:26.544
To any of them.

49:27.215 --> 49:29.877
But they keep dying all around me...

49:30.051 --> 49:32.508
...so I gotta be the guy, right?

49:33.847 --> 49:37.260
-Let's take them one at a time.
-Yeah, let's start with Amy Burley.

49:37.433 --> 49:40.266
That ought to be fresh
in your so-called mind.

49:43.481 --> 49:45.017
I took V.

49:45.733 --> 49:48.691
Not with the others, just with her.
We both did.

49:48.862 --> 49:51.228
V? Jason, Jason.

49:51.614 --> 49:53.275
I knew it.

49:55.785 --> 49:57.696
When I woke up...

49:58.997 --> 50:00.828
...Amy was....

50:01.708 --> 50:04.450
-Well, like she was.
-"Dead" is the word you're looking for.

50:04.627 --> 50:06.879
Stone-cold dead.

50:10.425 --> 50:12.916
We were alone in the house.

50:16.055 --> 50:18.341
God, I must have done it.

50:20.476 --> 50:22.637
But I don't know why.

50:23.313 --> 50:25.554
Honest to God, I loved her.

50:25.732 --> 50:27.222
Bullshit.

50:27.400 --> 50:28.936
You hated Maudette.

50:29.110 --> 50:32.147
-You hated Dawn.
-I didn't hate them.

50:32.572 --> 50:38.238
I mean, we had some pretty good times. It
was fucking and fighting, like with any girl.

50:40.413 --> 50:44.656
I just-- I don't understand
what would have made me do it.

50:46.544 --> 50:48.455
Your grandmother
knew what you were like.

50:48.630 --> 50:51.212
She guessed, she called you out.
You grabbed a knife.

50:51.382 --> 50:53.589
No, I didn't kill Gran...

50:53.760 --> 50:55.421
...and you know it.

50:55.595 --> 50:57.460
You better damn well find who did.

50:57.639 --> 51:00.096
This is the worst confession
I ever heard in my life.

51:00.266 --> 51:02.552
Fuck you, Andy. That's all I got.

51:14.155 --> 51:15.565
Look...

51:16.783 --> 51:19.570
...I don't wanna hurt nobody else.

51:21.246 --> 51:22.406
Lock me up.

51:24.249 --> 51:26.240
For chrissake, lock me up.

51:27.919 --> 51:29.955
Not before we get some solid facts.

51:31.172 --> 51:33.254
We'll waterboard you
if that's what it takes.

51:33.424 --> 51:34.459
-Andy.
-What?

51:34.634 --> 51:36.340
Lock him up.

51:43.726 --> 51:46.513
Come on, now.
About time you found the law.

51:46.688 --> 51:50.306
Hey, you. Wake up.
I know it's early, but I gotta tell you--

51:50.483 --> 51:51.848
Wait. Somebody's coming.

51:58.783 --> 52:00.990
Girl, guess what?

52:01.160 --> 52:03.537
Jason Stackhouse is the murderer.

52:03.705 --> 52:08.119
Yes, I swear. He's looking all crazy
in a hot way, you know him.

52:08.293 --> 52:11.535
But they're throwing him
in a cell right now.

52:12.213 --> 52:15.296
We are so lucky he didn't kill us.
